src_text: khabinete yi hlangane eNdlwini ya Vuendzi ya Phuresidente ya Sefako M Makgatho ePitori hi Ravumbirhi 1 Mhawuri 201 Swibohonkulu swa Khabinete Afrika-Dzonga yi lemuka N'hweti ya Vamanana hi Mhawuri, tanihi ku tlangela ku tlula 20 000 wa vamanana lava nga macha ku ya eUnion Buildings hi ti 9 Mhawuri 1956 va ri karhi va machela ku engeteleriwa ka milawu ya mapasa eka vamananSiku ra Rixaka ra Vamanana ri ta tlangeriwa eXitediyamu xa Galeshewe, eKimberley eKapa-N'walung Khabinete yi pasisile nhlokomhaka ya ku tlangela ya lembe leri ku va yi ri "Lembe ra OR Tambo: Vun'we bya Vamanana eka ku yisa Afrika-Dzonga emahlwen" Khabinete ri rhamba MaAfrika-Dzonga ku tirhisa n'hweti ya Mhawuri ku tkangela mitirho ya vamanana eka vaak Khabinete yi runguleriwile hi phurogireme ya malembe ya nharhu leyi nga ta hangalasiwa ya Nhlanganowa Vuyelerisa Mahanyela ya Khale (MRM).

src_text: IMC yi ta yisa swikombelo swa ku rhurhela swa RWC swa 2023 na ku tiyisisa leswaku tiko ra vuyeriwa hi swa ikhonomi ku suka eka ntlangu low Holobye wa Mitlangu na Vuhungasi, Tat Thulas Nxesi, u ta khoma nhlengeletano yo hambana na vahangasamahungunyingi ku vachumbutela hi purosese ya xikombelo xo rhurhel Khabinete yi pasisile Mpfapfarhuto wa Vun'winyi bya Tinhundzu (IP) wa Afrika-Dzonga - Xiyenge xa I (2017) ku va xihangalasiwa eka Gazete ya Mfumo ku va vaaki va nyika mavonelLeswi i ku angula eka xikombelo xa Kungu ra Nhluvukiso wa Tiko ku tshikeleriwa swinene vundlandlamuxi, antswisa mivuyelo, ku engeteleriwa ka ntshikelelo wa ikhonomi ya vutivi, na ku tirha swinene ku vuyeriwa eka ku ringanisa na ku phikizanPholisi ya IP i xitirho eka pholisi ya nkoka eka ku hlohlotela vundlandlamuxi, ku hundziseriwa ka thekinoloji, vulavisisi na nhluvukiso, nhlamuselo ya vutshila, nsirhelelo wa vatirhisi, nhluvukiso wa tifeme na hi ku anama, ku kula ka ikhonom Khabinete yi pasisisle mpfapfarhuto wa Qhinga ra Vitleketli ra Swiringanyeo ku va ri hangalasiwa ku kuma swibumabumel Qhinga ku ta rin'wana ra yinhla ya nhluvukiso wa pholisi eka sekithara ya vutleketli loko swi ta eka mmisi ya GH Xikongomelo xa kungu leri i ku hunguta ku khumbheka ko ka ku nga ri kahle eka mabngu hi vutleketli loko hi ri karhi hu lulamisa swilaveko swa sweswi na swa nkarhi lowu taka swa vutleketli hi ku landzelela nhluvukiso lowu tiyekSisiteme ya vutleketli hi yna hi nga khoma migingiriko ya ikhonomi na vaaku va Afrika-Dzonga hi ku kotisa ku fambafambisa vanhu na tinhundz Hambiswiritano, mmisi leyi humaka eka sekithara ya vutleketli yi vanga 1 ya mmisi ya tiko ya mimoya leyi yaka exibakabakeni (GHG), loko vutleketli bya magondzo byi endlaka 9 wa mimoya leyi ya GH
trg_text: The Minister of Home Affairs, Prof Hlengiwe Mkhize, will hold a separate briefing to explain the conditions and the process to be followed once the reapplication open Cabinet approved the South African Mint Company s designs for the 2017 commemorative colour coins series: Flowers and Birds of the Cape West Coast Biosphere Reserv This is an addition to the commemorative and circulation coin ranges to be issued in 201 Bills Cabinet approved publication of the Deeds Registries Amendment Bill of 2017 for public comment It amends the Deeds Registries Act, 1937 (Act 47 of 1937), so as to improve and enhance application and implementation of the Ac The Bill will also streamline and enhance the administration and registration of deeds Condolences Cabinet expressed its condolences to the families of the two soccer fans who lost their lives during the stampede at the FNB Stadium on Saturday, 29 July 2017.

src_text: Afrika-Dzonga ri tibohile ku hunguta mmisi ya ya vutleketlihi 34% hi 2020 na 42% hi 2026.
trg_text: Phase I (2017) for publication in the Government Gazette for public commentThis responds to the National Development Plan s call for greater emphasis on innovation, improved productivity, more intense pursuit of a knowledge economy, and better exploitation of comparative and competitive advantageThe IP Policy is an important policy instrument in promoting innovation, technology transfer, research and development, creative expression, consumer protection, industrial development and more broadly, economic growt Cabinet approved the Draft Green Transport Strategy to be published for public comment This strategy will form the cornerstone of policy development within the transport sector regarding the lowering of the GHG emission The aim of this strategy is to minimize the adverse impact of transport on the environment while addressing current and future transport demands based on sustainable development principleTransport systems form the backbone of South Africa s socio-economic activities by enabling the movement of people and good However, emissions from the transport sector account for 1 of the country s total greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions, with road transport being responsible for 9 of these GHG emission South Africa has pledged a GHG emissions reduction target of 34% by 2020 and 42% by 2026.
